# Styling

## Organization
- Styles are located in [src/assets/](mdc:src/assets) and [src/assets/css/](mdc:src/assets/css).
- SCSS is used for variables and shared styles ([variables.scss](mdc:src/assets/css/variables.scss), [common.scss](mdc:src/assets/css/common.scss)).
- [prime.css](mdc:src/assets/prime.css) is included for PrimeVue theming.
- Global styles can be added in [src/style.css](mdc:src/style.css).

## Conventions
- Use SCSS for variables and shared styles.
- Use BEM or feature-based class naming for custom styles.
- Import only the styles needed in each component.

## Example
- [variables.scss](mdc:src/assets/css/variables.scss): SCSS variables.
- [common.scss](mdc:src/assets/css/common.scss): Shared SCSS styles.
